==English==
===Etymology===
From Latin [[fructus]] (meaning "fruit") + [[-ose]] (meaning sugar and der. of [[sucrose]])
===Noun===
'''fructose'''
#A [[monosaccharide]] [[ketose]] [[sugar]], formula C<sub>6</sub>H<sub>12</sub>O<sub>6</sub>.


====Translations====
*Chinese: [[果糖]] guǒ táng 
*French: fructose ''m''
*Japanese: [[フルクトース]] ''furukutōsu'', [[果糖]] ([[かとう]] ''katō'')
*Korean: [[과당]] ''gwatang''
*Lithuanian: [[fruktozė]] ''f''

